flow.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap></p><p>For the discrimination of glioblastomas from metastases by analyzing perifocal T2-hyperintense regions, perfusion MRI had higher predictive values than MRSI (Table E-8). For Q2TIPS ASL MRI, sensitivity was 100&#x00025;, specificity was 71&#x00025;, PPV was 94&#x00025;, and NPV was 100&#x00025;, with a threshold value of 0.5 for rrCBF in perifocal T2-hyperintense regions (<xref ref-type="table" rid="T3">Table 3</xref>). Results of the Q2TIPS ASL sequence were slightly better than results of the ITS-FAIR ASL sequence (Table E-8).</p><p>Results for glioma grading are given in
